The newly appointed Vice Chancellor of the University of Maiduguri, Prof. Aliyu Shugaba, will on Saturday, August 3, 2019, be conferred with the fellowship award and Icon of Excellent Diplomatic Leadership and Management Award of the Institute of Business Diplomacy and Financial Management of Nigeria (IBDFM). Speaking to newsmen in Abuja, Registrar and Secretary to the Council of the Institute, Mr. Sukana Danjuma Tusha, confirmed that the decision to confer the dual prestigious awards on Prof. Aliyu Shugaba was reached after an extensive consideration of his sterling leadership and management qualities as demonstrated by the numerous development strides geared towards moving the University to a world-class status. Speaking further, the Registrar said that by these well deserved awards, the Vice Chancellor, University of Maiduguri, Prof. Aliyu Shugaba, will not only be the first Vice Chancellor in Nigeria to bag these awards, but the first to earn the award of Icon of Excellent Diplomatic Leadership and Management in addition to the prestigious Fellowship Award of the Institute. The programme is the 17th edition in the series, titled “ Managing Emotions in the Workplace.” UNIMAID gets new VC ICAN signs agreement with Malaysian university UNIMAID gets new VC Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin